# Equipment Quality

Not all swords are created equal. The blade forged by master smith with finest steel performs noticeably better than mass-produced weapon hammered from scrap iron. Equipment quality represents this variation—the difference between crude, functional, excellent, and legendary craftsmanship.

Quality affects mundane equipment before magical enchantment. A fine longsword grants bonuses through superior balance and edge retention, not magic. Quality represents craftsmanship, materials, and the skill of whoever created it.

Understanding quality tiers helps you make informed purchasing decisions, recognize exceptional gear when you find it, and know when that rusty sword really is as bad as it looks.

