## Choosing Equipment Quality

### Starting Equipment

Most characters begin with standard quality:

**Typical starting wealth:** 20-40 gold
**Standard longsword cost:** 15 gold
**Fine longsword cost:** 75 gold (prohibitively expensive)
**Masterwork longsword:** 150 gold (impossible for starting characters)

Early campaign, standard equipment is appropriate. Save money for consumables, adventuring gear, and armor upgrades.

### When to Upgrade

Invest in quality when you can afford it and need performance:

**Session 3-5:** Fine weapons for primary combatants (if you've accumulated 50-100 gold)
**Session 6-8:** Masterwork weapons or fine armor for specialists
**Session 10+:** Legendary equipment through quests, not purchase

Don't buy quality upgrades before you have basic defensive gear. Fine longsword doesn't help when you're unarmored and dying.

### Which Equipment to Upgrade First

Prioritize based on usage frequency:

**Primary weapon** (used every combat) > **Armor** (worn constantly) > **Secondary weapon** (situational) > **Tools** (used occasionally)

The weapon you swing every round benefits most from quality. Tools used twice per session can stay standard quality.

