## Quality vs. Magical Enhancement

### Key Differences

**Quality (Mundane):**
- Represents superior craftsmanship
- Available for purchase (except Legendary)
- Works for anyone who uses equipment
- Stacks with magical enhancement

**Magical Enhancement:**
- Supernatural power imbued in item
- Usually found as treasure, not purchased
- Properties beyond normal materials
- Can be applied to any quality tier

### Stacking Quality and Magic

Quality bonuses stack with magical enhancement:

**Masterwork Longsword:** +1 to hit and damage (quality)
**+1 Masterwork Longsword:** +2 to hit, +2 damage (quality + magic stack)
**+2 Fine Longsword:** +3 to hit OR +3 damage (quality + magic stack)

This stacking creates highly effective equipment, but costs accumulate rapidly. +1 masterwork longsword costs 150 (masterwork) + 600 (enchantment) = 750 gold minimum.

### When to Pursue Each

**Early campaign:** Standard equipment, save for armor/consumables
**Mid campaign:** Fine/Masterwork primary weapons before magical enhancement
**Late campaign:** Magical enhancement on already-quality equipment

A +1 enhancement on fine weapon (total +2) costs less than +2 enhancement on standard weapon and provides same benefit.

