## Obtaining Quality Equipment

### Purchase

Standard, Crude, and Fine equipment can be purchased in most cities:

**General stores:** Standard and Crude
**Smiths and craftspeople:** Standard and Fine
**Specialist artisans:** Fine and (commissioned) Masterwork

Masterwork requires commission—finding master smith, placing order, waiting weeks or months for completion. Not purchased off shelf.

### Quests and Rewards

Quality equipment makes excellent quest rewards:

**Minor quest:** Fine weapon or armor
**Moderate quest:** Masterwork weapon or armor
**Major quest:** Legendary equipment with unique properties

Game Masters can award quality equipment as treasure without unbalancing wealth—fine longsword worth 75 gold but only costs GM narrative approval.

### Crafting

Characters with appropriate craft skills can create quality equipment:

**Standard:** TN 8, requires appropriate tools and materials
**Fine:** TN 10, requires fine materials and considerable time
**Masterwork:** TN 12, requires rare materials and weeks of work

Crafting quality equipment provides cost savings (only pay material costs) but requires significant skill investment and campaign time.

